iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cairo - &nbsp;Egyptian officials say gunmen opened fire on a police checkpoint near the famed Saint Catherine's Monastery in Sinai, killing one policeman and wounding four.Security and medical officials say the policemen were manning the checkpoint outside the monastery in the southern part of the Sinai Peninsula when the attack took place on Tuesday night.The officials spoke on condition of anonymity under regulations.No further details were immediately available and government officials in Cairo couldn't be reached for comment. No one claimed responsibility for the attack.Earlier this month suicide bombers attacked two churches in the Nile Delta city of Tanta and the coastal city of Alexandria, killing 45 people on Palm Sunday.Egypt's Sinai-based Islamic State affiliate claimed responsibility for those attacks.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.